Detailed Description

LibraryRefGenerator is used to create a VLNV reference.

This function is used to create references in IP-Xact that are based in VLNV. This can be used to control spirit:libraryRefType in IP-Xact.

VLNV * LibraryRefGenerator::getVLNV ( VLNV::IPXactType  type  ) 

Generate a vlnv that matches the user inputs.

If one of the vlnv elements is empty then a null pointer is returned. This class gives the ownership of the generated VLNV to the caller of this function.
